\begin{document}
}{}$$\Delta {\rm CCI} = \displaystyle{{x - {\rm min}} \over {{\rm max} - {\rm min}}}$$\end{document}ΔCCI=x−minmax−min
where x was the observed CCI values, max and min were the sample maximum and minimum of CCI in each growing stage.

Yang et al. (2004) reported that PAR was 50% of the total incident solar radiation (R), and the amount of PAR that was intercepted by the plant canopy can be computed using the following exponential function:
(2)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
