\begin{document}
}{}$${\rm Model }1:{\rm PA}{{\rm R}_i} = {\rm }\Sigma \,0.5R{\rm }\left( {1{\rm }- {\rm }{e^{ - k{\rm LAI}}}} \right)$$\end{document}Model1:PARi=Σ0.5R(1−e−kLAI)
where R is the incoming total solar radiation (MJ m−2 d−1), k is the light extinction coefficient, which equals 0.60 for rice from Monteith (1969), and LAI (m2 leaf m−2 ground).

Here, we propose and evaluate a modification to the model of Yang et al. (2004) that accounts for the effects of variations in leaf chlorophyll content as follows:
